<DOC><DOCNO> AP890213-0217 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-02-13-89 0153EST</FILEID><FIRST>a a BC-SPE--Fashion:Bodywear     02-13 0116</FIRST><SECOND>BC-SPE--Fashion: Bodywear,0117</SECOND><HEAD>SPECIAL EDITION</HEAD><HEAD>Fashion: Bodywear</HEAD><HEAD>LaserPhoto NY709</HEAD><BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE><TEXT>   Like other active-sports gear, the body-hugging costumes worn bydancers, swimmers and bikers have been appropriated as fashionablestreetwear for teens and near-teens.   The old reasons for skintight outfits in sports and dance arefree movement and to cut down wind or water resistance. A new reasonmight be that, coupled with brilliant colors, the new clothes flaunta trim figure.   Designer Bonnie August couples a short, loose graffiti T-shirtwith second-skin bike pants, both done up with flashy neon colors.She also uses leotards, tank suits, crop tops, and stirrup tights incombinations of cotton blends, spandex, and shiny ribbed synthetics.</TEXT></DOC>